WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:33.742 --> 00:00:34.784 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:00:36.077 --> 00:00:37.996 position:50% align:center
There's no color.

00:00:38.079 --> 00:00:40.540 position:50% align:center
What? But that's not possible!

00:00:40.623 --> 00:00:42.208 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:00:42.292 --> 00:00:43.543 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 11A]
Look over there!

00:00:43.626 --> 00:00:44.669 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 11B]
What is that?

00:00:47.172 --> 00:00:48.340 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 11C]
Is this for real?

00:00:48.423 --> 00:00:50.425 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS chattering]

00:00:53.845 --> 00:00:54.763 position:50% align:center
Wow.

00:00:54.846 --> 00:00:55.930 position:50% align:center
No way.

00:00:57.515 --> 00:00:58.767 position:50% align:center
What is it?

00:01:12.030 --> 00:01:14.199 position:50% align:center
I... I don't believe it.

00:01:14.282 --> 00:01:15.283 position:50% align:center
Now what?

00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:22.415 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC] In terms of resources,
this city's a goldmine.

00:01:22.499 --> 00:01:25.043 position:50% align:center
Once my perfect golem
reaches completion,

00:01:25.126 --> 00:01:28.838 position:50% align:center
there won't be anyone
to stand in my way.

00:01:28.922 --> 00:01:30.757 position:50% align:center
Since I have infinite
time and no shortage

00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:35.512 position:50% align:center
of materials to work with,
let the experimentation begin.

00:01:35.595 --> 00:01:37.681 position:50% align:center
Just a bit longer.

00:01:37.764 --> 00:01:39.140 position:50% align:center
A little longer.

00:01:48.316 --> 00:01:51.111 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR] You mean your
goal all along was to become

00:01:51.194 --> 00:01:53.071 position:50% align:center
this thing?

00:01:53.154 --> 00:01:54.781 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC]
That is correct.

00:02:04.958 --> 00:02:07.252 position:50% align:center
I've obtained my
blood line's ultimate wish.

00:02:07.335 --> 00:02:09.671 position:50% align:center
The Rosenthals spent
generations profaning life

00:02:09.754 --> 00:02:12.007 position:50% align:center
and bending the rules of death
so one day we could attain

00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:14.092 position:50% align:center
the form of the god
you see before you!

00:02:14.175 --> 00:02:15.260 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Huh?

00:02:15.343 --> 00:02:17.053 position:50% align:center
A being unlike any
other that's existed,

00:02:17.137 --> 00:02:18.972 position:50% align:center
possessing a perfect
soul and body.

00:02:19.055 --> 00:02:21.182 position:50% align:center
This is a god! This is me!

00:02:21.266 --> 00:02:22.600 position:50% align:center
That's ridiculous.

00:02:22.684 --> 00:02:24.769 position:50% align:center
Go and do this crap
someplace else.

00:02:24.853 --> 00:02:26.646 position:50% align:center
Who are you calling ridiculous?

00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:29.774 position:50% align:center
You people have been
pursuing the same goal as me.

00:02:29.858 --> 00:02:31.985 position:50% align:center
Pushing for an individual
who is not a deity

00:02:32.068 --> 00:02:33.820 position:50% align:center
to achieve a celestial purpose.

00:02:33.903 --> 00:02:35.488 position:50% align:center
In your case, a Level Six.

00:02:35.572 --> 00:02:37.615 position:50% align:center
There's no difference
between you and I.

00:02:37.699 --> 00:02:40.118 position:50% align:center
I'm not interested
in the slightest.

00:02:40.201 --> 00:02:42.662 position:50% align:center
Though there's no shortage
of scumbags researching it

00:02:42.746 --> 00:02:43.580 position:50% align:center
like crazy.

00:02:43.663 --> 00:02:44.664 position:50% align:center
In that case,

00:02:44.748 --> 00:02:46.499 position:50% align:center
I'm appreciative
since their data proved

00:02:46.583 --> 00:02:49.294 position:50% align:center
tremendously helpful for
advancing my end goal.

00:02:49.377 --> 00:02:52.088 position:50% align:center
I've searched all over the
world for one particular thing

00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:54.132 position:50% align:center
only to discover
it resided here.

00:02:54.215 --> 00:02:56.801 position:50% align:center
This was the only place I
was able to find the memories

00:02:56.885 --> 00:02:58.845 position:50% align:center
of 10,031 deaths.

00:02:58.928 --> 00:03:00.013 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR gasps]

00:03:01.264 --> 00:03:05.101 position:50% align:center
Hey... what did you just say?

00:04:37.777 --> 00:04:39.529 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC]
I was close to becoming a god,

00:04:39.612 --> 00:04:41.364 position:50% align:center
but there was an
element missing.

00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:44.325 position:50% align:center
I required 10,000
dying memories.

00:04:44.409 --> 00:04:47.412 position:50% align:center
That was the most important
and difficult key to come by.

00:04:47.495 --> 00:04:50.623 position:50% align:center
All I can say is thank
heaven for Academy City!

00:04:50.707 --> 00:04:52.208 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR growls]

00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:53.835 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC chuckles]

00:04:53.918 --> 00:04:55.670 position:50% align:center
Hold on. You're the one!

00:04:55.754 --> 00:05:00.050 position:50% align:center
The person responsible for
the 10,031 dying memories.

00:05:00.133 --> 00:05:03.178 position:50% align:center
Ah, yes. Now I see. It is you.

00:05:03.261 --> 00:05:04.679 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR growls]

00:05:04.763 --> 00:05:06.806 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC] Did you know,
after looking through

00:05:06.890 --> 00:05:09.934 position:50% align:center
those dead girls' final
memories, they all feature you.

00:05:10.018 --> 00:05:13.355 position:50% align:center
A grisly monster come to
snuff them out of existence.

00:05:13.438 --> 00:05:15.440 position:50% align:center
Each and every one
meticulously recorded

00:05:15.523 --> 00:05:17.233 position:50% align:center
the unique way
you decided to cruelly

00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:19.778 position:50% align:center
and mercilessly butcher them.

00:05:19.861 --> 00:05:22.238 position:50% align:center
I'm impressed you
managed to kill so many.

00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:24.449 position:50% align:center
That's too much, even for me!

00:05:24.532 --> 00:05:26.701 position:50% align:center
I mean, to do something
as gruesome as murdering

00:05:26.785 --> 00:05:29.829 position:50% align:center
a teenage girl over 10,000
times for your own benefit,

00:05:29.913 --> 00:05:32.957 position:50% align:center
well... how am I not
supposed to respect you?

00:05:33.041 --> 00:05:36.127 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR] Screw you for
using their deaths on something

00:05:36.211 --> 00:05:37.879 position:50% align:center
as pointless as this!

00:05:43.426 --> 00:05:44.678 position:50% align:center
or anyone else.

00:05:44.761 --> 00:05:46.680 position:50% align:center
Like hell I'm gonna
let you steal them.

00:05:49.933 --> 00:05:52.268 position:50% align:center
And I'm definitely not
letting a monster like you

00:05:52.352 --> 00:05:54.020 position:50% align:center
use them however you please!

00:05:58.316 --> 00:05:59.442 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR growls]

00:06:01.569 --> 00:06:02.821 position:50% align:center
You're finished!

00:06:14.374 --> 00:06:15.834 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC]
There it is.

00:06:15.917 --> 00:06:19.546 position:50% align:center
That's the power responsible
for taking away all those lives.

00:06:19.629 --> 00:06:20.672 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Tch.

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:26.386 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC]
Sadly, it won't work against me.

00:06:31.891 --> 00:06:32.934 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR grunts]

00:06:36.021 --> 00:06:38.106 position:50% align:center
It doesn't matter how
many times you regenerate,

00:06:38.189 --> 00:06:40.650 position:50% align:center
I'll pulverize you till
there's nothing left.

00:06:43.862 --> 00:06:46.531 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC laughing]

00:06:46.614 --> 00:06:48.033 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC]
You're desperate!

00:06:48.116 --> 00:06:49.743 position:50% align:center
So desperate!

00:06:49.826 --> 00:06:51.911 position:50% align:center
Not like it'll do you any good.

00:06:58.543 --> 00:07:00.670 position:50% align:center
On that note,
I should take my leave.

00:07:00.754 --> 00:07:03.256 position:50% align:center
I still require a little more
time before I completely

00:07:03.340 --> 00:07:05.133 position:50% align:center
transcend to a god state.

00:07:05.216 --> 00:07:07.385 position:50% align:center
I suggest you and that
dimwitted family head

00:07:07.469 --> 00:07:09.387 position:50% align:center
leave the city
while you still can.

00:07:12.849 --> 00:07:13.850 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Tch.

00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:29.491 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER] This whole time,
what is it I've been doing

00:07:29.574 --> 00:07:31.117 position:50% align:center
with my life?

00:07:31.201 --> 00:07:33.495 position:50% align:center
[HIRUMI] I don't think you're
aware how personally responsible

00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:35.163 position:50% align:center
you are.
If you hadn't come here,

00:07:35.246 --> 00:07:37.332 position:50% align:center
this girl wouldn't have
taken her own life.

00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:40.710 position:50% align:center
How exactly do you think
those people died?

00:07:40.794 --> 00:07:43.254 position:50% align:center
Maybe it's because you spread
death wherever you travel.

00:07:43.338 --> 00:07:47.008 position:50% align:center
That's the entire point
of being a necromancer.

00:07:47.092 --> 00:07:49.844 position:50% align:center
You were born a Rosenthal
and this is just now

00:07:49.928 --> 00:07:51.304 position:50% align:center
occurring to you?

00:07:51.388 --> 00:07:53.264 position:50% align:center
You can't protect others.

00:07:55.350 --> 00:07:58.436 position:50% align:center
You're an utter failure
to the family name.

00:07:58.520 --> 00:08:01.439 position:50% align:center
Now, sit back and watch
as I fulfill our bloodline's

00:08:01.523 --> 00:08:02.816 position:50% align:center
ancient wish!

00:08:04.859 --> 00:08:08.196 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]
I couldn't protect anything.

00:08:08.279 --> 00:08:10.407 position:50% align:center
I've lost Hirumi.

00:08:10.490 --> 00:08:12.701 position:50% align:center
And all that remains
is the fact that the blame

00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:15.578 position:50% align:center
rests entirely with
the Rosenthals.

00:08:15.662 --> 00:08:18.707 position:50% align:center
Who am I? And what have I done?

00:08:18.790 --> 00:08:20.667 position:50% align:center
Why am I here?

00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:21.960 position:50% align:center
Am I...

00:08:22.043 --> 00:08:24.504 position:50% align:center
"After hard work and
overcoming many obstacles,

00:08:24.587 --> 00:08:27.215 position:50% align:center
Misaka was finally successful.

00:08:27.298 --> 00:08:28.842 position:50% align:center
It wasn't easy making them,

00:08:28.925 --> 00:08:32.554 position:50% align:center
but they turned out so
delicious, didn't they?"

00:08:32.637 --> 00:08:34.222 position:50% align:center
asks Misaka Misaka.

00:08:36.266 --> 00:08:38.643 position:50% align:center
"Sleep and keep having
those pleasant dreams.

00:08:38.727 --> 00:08:40.562 position:50% align:center
You need them more
than ever during times

00:08:40.645 --> 00:08:42.897 position:50% align:center
as dire as this,"

00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:45.316 position:50% align:center
says Misaka,
wishing the best for you.

00:08:53.366 --> 00:08:55.035 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046] "If this is
what the Rosenthal family

00:08:55.118 --> 00:08:57.662 position:50% align:center
really wanted, does that mean
the creature before us is

00:08:57.746 --> 00:09:00.665 position:50% align:center
the form of god they
spoke of?" says Misaka,

00:09:00.749 --> 00:09:02.500 position:50% align:center
unable to stop trembling.

00:09:02.584 --> 00:09:04.044 position:50% align:center
No, it is not.

00:09:04.127 --> 00:09:06.254 position:50% align:center
This is just some
scum bucket monster

00:09:06.338 --> 00:09:09.716 position:50% align:center
that's got squat to do with
the Rosenthals or anybody else.

00:09:11.634 --> 00:09:13.136 position:50% align:center
Adonai.

00:09:13.219 --> 00:09:14.304 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Hey!

00:09:14.387 --> 00:09:17.223 position:50% align:center
Are you gonna decide
what you wanna do?

00:09:17.307 --> 00:09:19.976 position:50% align:center
It's your life. Your decision.

00:09:20.060 --> 00:09:22.187 position:50% align:center
But if you plan on being a hero,

00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:25.440 position:50% align:center
don't get confused about
what you want to save.

00:09:25.523 --> 00:09:26.900 position:50% align:center
A hero?

00:09:26.983 --> 00:09:29.027 position:50% align:center
Someone who doesn't hesitate
to stretch out their hands

00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:30.362 position:50% align:center
and run as fast as they can

00:09:30.445 --> 00:09:32.405 position:50% align:center
towards what they're
trying to rescue.

00:09:32.489 --> 00:09:35.742 position:50% align:center
So the question is, what do you
want to save with your hands?

00:09:35.825 --> 00:09:36.951 position:50% align:center
If you don't know the answer,

00:09:37.035 --> 00:09:38.828 position:50% align:center
then you'll never
end up reaching it!

00:09:38.912 --> 00:09:40.205 position:50% align:center
I want...

00:09:44.042 --> 00:09:47.045 position:50% align:center
If I ever need anything,
swear you'll do it for me!

00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:49.839 position:50% align:center
"Anything"? Do you think you
could be a bit more specific?

00:09:49.923 --> 00:09:52.509 position:50% align:center
Promise me!
Promise me now, Esther!

00:09:52.592 --> 00:09:53.510 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]
Promise you?

00:09:53.593 --> 00:09:56.012 position:50% align:center
[HIRUMI]
That's right. Like this.

00:09:56.096 --> 00:09:58.932 position:50% align:center
If you think I'm messing around,
then this is your wake-up call.

00:09:59.015 --> 00:10:00.475 position:50% align:center
I'll save Hirumi at any cost,

00:10:00.558 --> 00:10:02.560 position:50% align:center
and if you think you can
take our lives and use them

00:10:02.644 --> 00:10:06.147 position:50% align:center
for your own purposes,
you've got another thing coming!

00:10:06.231 --> 00:10:07.732 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]
Found it.

00:10:07.816 --> 00:10:09.651 position:50% align:center
What I want to save.

00:10:09.734 --> 00:10:11.736 position:50% align:center
What I want to protect.

00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:13.780 position:50% align:center
I want...

00:10:13.863 --> 00:10:16.491 position:50% align:center
Master. I have a favor to ask.

00:10:16.574 --> 00:10:17.992 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Huh?

00:10:18.076 --> 00:10:20.495 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER] This devil that's
tampering with life and death.

00:10:20.578 --> 00:10:22.330 position:50% align:center
If we're going to defeat it...

00:10:26.126 --> 00:10:28.878 position:50% align:center
...then I'm going
to need you to help me.

00:10:28.962 --> 00:10:30.672 position:50% align:center
Now you're talking.

00:10:30.755 --> 00:10:33.133 position:50% align:center
Houtou. I need you
to fight alongside me.

00:10:33.216 --> 00:10:35.218 position:50% align:center
[HOUTOU]
As you order, Adonai.

00:10:36.761 --> 00:10:38.680 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
What're we waiting for?

00:10:38.763 --> 00:10:40.181 position:50% align:center
Let's kick its ass.

00:10:40.265 --> 00:10:42.017 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]
Yeah.

00:10:42.100 --> 00:10:43.685 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Stay here and do whatever.

00:10:43.768 --> 00:10:46.104 position:50% align:center
Make penance for what
you've done. I don't care.

00:10:51.568 --> 00:10:53.319 position:50% align:center
Looks like the thing's
changing shape.

00:10:53.403 --> 00:10:55.655 position:50% align:center
Is it me or is it
growing in size?

00:10:55.739 --> 00:10:58.199 position:50% align:center
And they still just want
us to shut up and watch?

00:10:58.283 --> 00:11:00.535 position:50% align:center
We have to try something
before it's too late!

00:11:00.618 --> 00:11:02.662 position:50% align:center
We haven't received clearance
from the governing board

00:11:02.746 --> 00:11:03.913 position:50% align:center
to engage yet!

00:11:03.997 --> 00:11:06.082 position:50% align:center
--[YOMIKAWA] Yeah, but...
--Easy, Yomikawa.

00:11:06.166 --> 00:11:07.876 position:50% align:center
What good is charging in
when we don't know

00:11:07.959 --> 00:11:09.627 position:50% align:center
what we're dealing with?

00:11:09.711 --> 00:11:10.837 position:50% align:center
Hey, Ito.

00:11:10.920 --> 00:11:11.921 position:50% align:center
Send up the drone.

00:11:12.005 --> 00:11:13.840 position:50% align:center
We need to get a better look.

00:11:13.923 --> 00:11:15.842 position:50% align:center
They said we couldn't go inside,

00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:18.303 position:50% align:center
but didn't say anything
about surveilling it.

00:11:18.386 --> 00:11:19.471 position:50% align:center
All right, then.

00:11:35.403 --> 00:11:37.864 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR] How'd you
manage to get ahead of us?

00:11:37.947 --> 00:11:39.032 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA chuckles]

00:11:39.115 --> 00:11:41.117 position:50% align:center
You're one tough bastard.

00:11:41.201 --> 00:11:43.078 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA] I have all kinds
of hidden supply routes

00:11:43.161 --> 00:11:47.207 position:50% align:center
in this school to transport
materials for my experiments.

00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:49.793 position:50% align:center
Besides, I can't die yet.

00:11:49.876 --> 00:11:54.631 position:50% align:center
Not while the bastard
who took Hirumi... is free.

00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:56.841 position:50% align:center
Like I'll let him
get away with it.

00:11:56.925 --> 00:11:58.093 position:50% align:center
"That thing.

00:11:58.176 --> 00:12:01.596 position:50% align:center
Is there a way we can
defeat it?" says Misaka,

00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:04.349 position:50% align:center
doubting we'd ever be able
to gain victory over an enemy

00:12:04.432 --> 00:12:06.351 position:50% align:center
this monstrous.

00:12:06.434 --> 00:12:07.936 position:50% align:center
There's a way.

00:12:08.019 --> 00:12:10.855 position:50% align:center
As long as I have
Emperor Shun's Blade.

00:12:10.939 --> 00:12:13.149 position:50% align:center
This knife, it carries
magic that can disrupt

00:12:13.233 --> 00:12:14.734 position:50% align:center
Taowu's pseudo-soul.

00:12:16.069 --> 00:12:19.614 position:50% align:center
Think of it as a poison designed
specifically for its spirit.

00:12:19.698 --> 00:12:22.450 position:50% align:center
I just have to bring it in
contact with Taowu's charm.

00:12:23.952 --> 00:12:26.705 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC screams]

00:12:26.788 --> 00:12:28.873 position:50% align:center
But this is going
to be far from easy.

00:12:28.957 --> 00:12:30.625 position:50% align:center
Now that her body
is so grotesque,

00:12:30.709 --> 00:12:33.169 position:50% align:center
pinpointing the location of
the charm will prove difficult.

00:12:33.253 --> 00:12:34.671 position:50% align:center
Don't overthink this.

00:12:34.754 --> 00:12:37.632 position:50% align:center
I say we just explode its
entire body and call it a day.

00:12:37.716 --> 00:12:39.759 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER] I'm sorry, Master,
but that won't work.

00:12:39.843 --> 00:12:41.386 position:50% align:center
Why not?

00:12:41.469 --> 00:12:43.513 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER] Even if we did
blast it using your power,

00:12:43.596 --> 00:12:45.890 position:50% align:center
as long as the pseudo-soul
charm is intact,

00:12:45.974 --> 00:12:47.892 position:50% align:center
the body will keep regenerating.

00:12:47.976 --> 00:12:49.227 position:50% align:center
Fine.

00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:51.062 position:50% align:center
Not sure I get it, but it
sounds like one of those

00:12:51.146 --> 00:12:52.522 position:50% align:center
kill-the-core deals.

00:12:52.605 --> 00:12:55.275 position:50% align:center
Yes! That's what it means.
I knew you would understand!

00:12:55.358 --> 00:12:57.694 position:50% align:center
Since it sounds like you
two are on the same page

00:12:57.777 --> 00:12:59.821 position:50% align:center
regarding strategy,
how about I lead you

00:12:59.904 --> 00:13:02.323 position:50% align:center
to where that monster is
so you can get revenge

00:13:02.407 --> 00:13:03.825 position:50% align:center
for me and Hirumi?

00:13:09.330 --> 00:13:10.957 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA chuckles]

00:13:11.041 --> 00:13:12.167 position:50% align:center
Hishigata.

00:13:18.757 --> 00:13:19.924 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
No games.

00:13:20.008 --> 00:13:22.385 position:50% align:center
You better be showing us
how to reach its body.

00:13:22.469 --> 00:13:23.678 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
Look around you.

00:13:23.762 --> 00:13:25.972 position:50% align:center
That thing is
assimilating the school.

00:13:26.056 --> 00:13:30.018 position:50% align:center
If we use my supply routes,
we should be able to get close.

00:13:30.101 --> 00:13:33.188 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER] But if you continue
moving, then you'll...

00:13:33.271 --> 00:13:34.689 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA]
It's okay.

00:13:34.773 --> 00:13:36.524 position:50% align:center
I'm going to die anyway.

00:13:38.234 --> 00:13:41.112 position:50% align:center
But before that happens...

00:13:41.196 --> 00:13:43.198 position:50% align:center
...I have to get her back.

00:13:43.281 --> 00:13:44.783 position:50% align:center
My precious Hirumi.

00:13:47.619 --> 00:13:49.954 position:50% align:center
If you're going to
do this, then be quick.

00:13:50.038 --> 00:13:51.998 position:50% align:center
According to my research,
its body has grown

00:13:52.082 --> 00:13:54.334 position:50% align:center
to such an immense size,
it won't be long before

00:13:54.417 --> 00:13:57.212 position:50% align:center
the thing swells up and
reaches its perfect form.

00:13:57.295 --> 00:14:00.006 position:50% align:center
The old turning-good-before
you-die cliché, huh?

00:14:00.090 --> 00:14:02.008 position:50% align:center
A little late to
atone for your sins.

00:14:02.092 --> 00:14:04.010 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA chuckles]
I still don't feel guilty

00:14:04.094 --> 00:14:05.345 position:50% align:center
for what happened,

00:14:05.428 --> 00:14:07.681 position:50% align:center
but Hirumi is mine and
I won't let even the devil

00:14:07.764 --> 00:14:08.973 position:50% align:center
take her from me.

00:14:09.057 --> 00:14:10.600 position:50% align:center
Your sister is...

00:14:10.684 --> 00:14:12.602 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Doesn't really matter.

00:14:12.686 --> 00:14:14.979 position:50% align:center
Evil or not, everybody's
got one thing in life

00:14:15.063 --> 00:14:16.398 position:50% align:center
they're not willing to budge on.

00:14:16.481 --> 00:14:19.275 position:50% align:center
[HISHIGATA chuckles]
See? He understands. Heh.

00:14:28.410 --> 00:14:30.078 position:50% align:center
Man, that's disgusting.

00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:31.996 position:50% align:center
It's moving around
inside the walls.

00:14:32.080 --> 00:14:34.290 position:50% align:center
The most frustrating part
is whoever or whatever's

00:14:34.374 --> 00:14:36.042 position:50% align:center
controlling that life form,
we don't know

00:14:36.126 --> 00:14:37.419 position:50% align:center
what their goal is.

00:14:59.816 --> 00:15:01.526 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046 gasps]

00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:09.701 position:50% align:center
"It looks like it's gotten
bigger," says Misaka,

00:15:09.784 --> 00:15:13.580 position:50% align:center
anxiously glancing around
at her surroundings.

00:15:13.663 --> 00:15:14.914 position:50% align:center
What? You scared?

00:15:14.998 --> 00:15:17.625 position:50% align:center
"Everything is all right,"
responds Misaka,

00:15:17.709 --> 00:15:21.129 position:50% align:center
concerned she is not successful
in concealing her worry.

00:15:21.212 --> 00:15:23.757 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR] This is a
battle between villains.

00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:27.093 position:50% align:center
Since you're not one,
hang back and keep quiet.

00:15:51.910 --> 00:15:53.578 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC] Just strolling
around inside of me

00:15:53.661 --> 00:15:55.288 position:50% align:center
like you own the place?

00:15:55.372 --> 00:15:58.166 position:50% align:center
Meanwhile, my physical
form is still evolving.

00:15:58.249 --> 00:16:01.127 position:50% align:center
The current family head is
too polite to tell them to wait

00:16:01.211 --> 00:16:02.796 position:50% align:center
and is going to
end up interfering

00:16:02.879 --> 00:16:05.173 position:50% align:center
with her own ancestor.

00:16:05.256 --> 00:16:06.424 position:50% align:center
What a pain.

00:16:06.508 --> 00:16:09.094 position:50% align:center
My descendants
truly are useless.

00:16:09.177 --> 00:16:10.220 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR gasps]

00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:13.223 position:50% align:center
[MISAKA 10046] "Is something
the matter?" Misaka asks,

00:16:13.306 --> 00:16:15.433 position:50% align:center
following your line of sight.

00:16:15.517 --> 00:16:16.685 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
It was nothing.

00:16:18.311 --> 00:16:20.480 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC]
Intuitive little bastard.

00:16:20.563 --> 00:16:23.316 position:50% align:center
Aw, what a pain!
An absolute pain!

00:16:25.026 --> 00:16:27.070 position:50% align:center
Why is this happening?!

00:16:27.153 --> 00:16:29.864 position:50% align:center
I thought a body of this size
would allow a perfect ability

00:16:29.948 --> 00:16:32.867 position:50% align:center
to reside within it already.

00:16:32.951 --> 00:16:34.953 position:50% align:center
I'm missing something.

00:16:35.036 --> 00:16:38.206 position:50% align:center
There's an element I still
need to complete this form.

00:16:39.833 --> 00:16:42.669 position:50% align:center
Guess I'll just have to try
out different methods then.

00:16:46.506 --> 00:16:48.383 position:50% align:center
I don't see any
sign of Anti-Skill.

00:16:48.466 --> 00:16:50.010 position:50% align:center
We must've driven them back.

00:16:50.093 --> 00:16:51.761 position:50% align:center
We have Hishigata
to thank for that.

00:16:51.845 --> 00:16:55.140 position:50% align:center
Whatever this new weapon is,
it's proved to be effective.

00:16:55.223 --> 00:16:56.933 position:50% align:center
[ALPHA TEAM 11A] Since we
have a moment, let's regroup

00:16:57.017 --> 00:16:58.935 position:50% align:center
but keep moving on. Let's go!

00:16:59.019 --> 00:17:01.479 position:50% align:center
[ALPHA TEAM screaming]

00:17:03.148 --> 00:17:05.191 position:50% align:center
[ALPHA TEAM screaming]

00:17:07.110 --> 00:17:08.903 position:50% align:center
This doesn't make sense!
We're on the same si--!

00:17:14.242 --> 00:17:16.202 position:50% align:center
Ah, yes!

00:17:16.286 --> 00:17:18.413 position:50% align:center
Now that's more like it!

00:17:18.496 --> 00:17:22.000 position:50% align:center
Perfect! I feel my
evolution accelerating!

00:17:22.083 --> 00:17:25.211 position:50% align:center
This is what I needed
to speed up the process!

00:17:25.295 --> 00:17:27.797 position:50% align:center
What if I was to
assimilate all of them?

00:17:31.718 --> 00:17:34.512 position:50% align:center
[ALPHA TEAM yelling]

00:17:37.057 --> 00:17:40.393 position:50% align:center
Our justice will never die,
even if our physical forms do--

00:17:40.477 --> 00:17:41.728 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:17:45.106 --> 00:17:45.899 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]

00:17:45.982 --> 00:17:48.693 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER 10A growls]

00:17:51.946 --> 00:17:53.281 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR laughs]

00:17:59.037 --> 00:18:01.414 position:50% align:center
What the hell made it
suddenly start attacking us?

00:18:01.498 --> 00:18:03.792 position:50% align:center
Did it decide it wanted
a meal or something?

00:18:03.875 --> 00:18:05.585 position:50% align:center
[ANTISKILL 11A]
HQ. This is Alpha.

00:18:05.669 --> 00:18:09.047 position:50% align:center
We have five DA in custody
and are heading to-- Damn!

00:18:09.130 --> 00:18:11.341 position:50% align:center
We're encountering some kind
of unidentified creatures!

00:18:11.424 --> 00:18:13.593 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER 10A growls]

00:18:13.677 --> 00:18:14.803 position:50% align:center
[ANTISKILL 11A]
Send backup--

00:18:14.886 --> 00:18:16.137 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:18:26.022 --> 00:18:27.732 position:50% align:center
[ALPHA TEAM 11I]
Help us!

00:18:27.816 --> 00:18:29.567 position:50% align:center
Grab my hand! Quick!

00:18:34.823 --> 00:18:36.533 position:50% align:center
[gunshots]

00:18:38.910 --> 00:18:40.203 position:50% align:center
Let's go!

00:18:40.286 --> 00:18:41.246 position:50% align:center
Hold it!

00:18:41.329 --> 00:18:42.706 position:50% align:center
Our orders are to...

00:18:45.667 --> 00:18:47.085 position:50% align:center
I'm going anyway.

00:18:47.168 --> 00:18:48.753 position:50% align:center
We can't just let
them get killed!

00:18:48.837 --> 00:18:49.963 position:50% align:center
I know, but...

00:18:50.046 --> 00:18:52.215 position:50% align:center
I'm a teacher first
and Anti-Skill second,

00:18:52.298 --> 00:18:54.217 position:50% align:center
and abandoning people
who're asking for help

00:18:54.300 --> 00:18:57.137 position:50% align:center
isn't something
I teach my students!

00:18:57.220 --> 00:18:58.555 position:50% align:center
She's got us there.

00:19:00.181 --> 00:19:01.266 position:50% align:center
Hey, wait!

00:19:07.313 --> 00:19:09.232 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER 10A growls]

00:19:11.609 --> 00:19:12.902 position:50% align:center
[YOMIKAWA]
Hurry and get outta there!

00:19:12.986 --> 00:19:14.529 position:50% align:center
[ALPHA TEAM 11K]
But you're with Anti-Skill!

00:19:14.612 --> 00:19:17.032 position:50% align:center
Now's not the time for us
to be fighting each other!

00:19:17.115 --> 00:19:18.783 position:50% align:center
[explosion]

00:19:18.867 --> 00:19:20.493 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER 10A growls]

00:19:29.377 --> 00:19:30.462 position:50% align:center
Yomikawa!

00:19:31.838 --> 00:19:32.922 position:50% align:center
Watch out, behind you!

00:19:33.006 --> 00:19:34.132 position:50% align:center
[ITO gasps]

00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:40.722 position:50% align:center
Then again, nobody's ordered
us not to save lives either.

00:19:40.805 --> 00:19:43.308 position:50% align:center
You're right.
Let's do our jobs as teachers.

00:19:43.391 --> 00:19:45.310 position:50% align:center
All right then,
let's get moving!

00:19:52.275 --> 00:19:53.777 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR growls]

00:20:02.952 --> 00:20:04.621 position:50% align:center
There's no end to these things!

00:20:06.081 --> 00:20:07.582 position:50% align:center
[GHOULS groaning]

00:20:10.627 --> 00:20:13.546 position:50% align:center
[GHOULS groaning]

00:20:20.595 --> 00:20:22.972 position:50% align:center
[GHOULS groaning]

00:20:23.056 --> 00:20:24.891 position:50% align:center
Somehow, they resurrected.

00:20:24.974 --> 00:20:27.143 position:50% align:center
Do they have pseudo-souls?

00:20:27.227 --> 00:20:28.895 position:50% align:center
No, something else.

00:20:28.978 --> 00:20:31.898 position:50% align:center
It's doesn't appear as
though they're alive either,

00:20:31.981 --> 00:20:33.775 position:50% align:center
and yet, they're still
able to move.

00:20:33.858 --> 00:20:36.569 position:50% align:center
This is power only
a god could wield.

00:20:36.653 --> 00:20:38.822 position:50% align:center
Makes you wonder if that
thing's already become one

00:20:38.905 --> 00:20:40.448 position:50% align:center
and we're too late to stop it.

00:20:40.532 --> 00:20:41.950 position:50% align:center
[GHOULS groaning]

00:20:42.033 --> 00:20:43.076 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
Tch.

00:20:49.499 --> 00:20:50.709 position:50% align:center
[GHOUL 11E grunts]

00:20:58.425 --> 00:21:00.385 position:50% align:center
[GHOUL 11E groaning]

00:21:03.471 --> 00:21:04.681 position:50% align:center
It's no use.

00:21:04.764 --> 00:21:06.808 position:50% align:center
I can't harm them.

00:21:06.891 --> 00:21:08.852 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR]
You might wannaa look away.

00:21:10.145 --> 00:21:11.271 position:50% align:center
[squish]

00:21:13.440 --> 00:21:15.817 position:50% align:center
All these guys were
already killed once before,

00:21:15.900 --> 00:21:17.402 position:50% align:center
remember?

00:21:17.485 --> 00:21:20.030 position:50% align:center
So what we've got here aren't
people; they're only corpses.

00:21:20.113 --> 00:21:21.156 position:50% align:center
[ESTHER]
Master.

00:21:21.239 --> 00:21:22.991 position:50% align:center
This isn't the work a hero does.

00:21:23.074 --> 00:21:26.453 position:50% align:center
This is more like a job
for a son-of-a-bitch villain.

00:21:31.499 --> 00:21:33.293 position:50% align:center
No one could've
imagined the word "hero"

00:21:33.376 --> 00:21:36.129 position:50% align:center
coming out of the mouth
of a villain like yourself.

00:21:36.212 --> 00:21:39.341 position:50% align:center
It's almost like you know
one, a bona-fide do-gooder.

00:21:39.424 --> 00:21:42.052 position:50% align:center
[ACCELERATOR] Tch. I'm going
to need you to stop bringing up

00:21:42.135 --> 00:21:43.386 position:50% align:center
worthless memories.

00:21:47.974 --> 00:21:49.184 position:50% align:center
Don't get too close!

00:21:49.267 --> 00:21:51.269 position:50% align:center
Keep engaging them
from a distance!

00:21:51.353 --> 00:21:52.354 position:50% align:center
Right!

00:21:54.689 --> 00:21:56.775 position:50% align:center
[ISAAC]
Amazing! Outstanding!

00:21:56.858 --> 00:21:58.985 position:50% align:center
This is the ultimate evolution!

00:21:59.069 --> 00:22:03.448 position:50% align:center
The Rosenthal's 400-year-old
wish is becoming a reality!

00:22:03.531 --> 00:22:06.076 position:50% align:center
I will reach the highest
level of existence!

00:22:06.159 --> 00:22:08.453 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:22:08.536 --> 00:22:11.956 position:50% align:center
No matter how many we defeat,
more of them keep popping up.

00:22:12.040 --> 00:22:15.001 position:50% align:center
How much further till we
reach this blob's main body?

00:22:15.085 --> 00:22:18.004 position:50% align:center
My readings are saying
it's close by, but...

00:22:18.088 --> 00:22:20.507 position:50% align:center
You're not taking into
account it's growing larger

00:22:20.590 --> 00:22:23.009 position:50% align:center
and acquiring new
powers every minute.

00:22:23.093 --> 00:22:25.595 position:50% align:center
The thing's evolution
is rapidly accelerating

00:22:25.679 --> 00:22:27.806 position:50% align:center
and you're running
out of time to defeat it.

00:22:29.683 --> 00:22:30.892 position:50% align:center
Great.

00:22:30.975 --> 00:22:32.977 position:50% align:center
Looks like I'm just about
out of time as well.